00:07:39.290 --> 00:07:41.600
Can you tell us about that moment

00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:43.440
when you decided to
run for Congress?

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:46.080
And what influenced your decision?

00:07:46.080 --> 00:07:47.660
&gt;&gt; Rep. Candice Miller: Well
I had 2 different moments

00:07:47.660 --> 00:07:50.390
because I ran in 80-- gosh.

00:07:50.390 --> 00:07:51.690
Isn't it terrible?

00:07:51.690 --> 00:07:54.780
I can't remember if
it was '84 or '86?

00:07:54.780 --> 00:07:56.080
I ran for Congress.

00:07:56.080 --> 00:07:57.380
I was 30 at the time,
trying to remember.

00:07:57.380 --> 00:08:01.600
So-- anyway and lost and lost.

00:08:01.600 --> 00:08:04.670
And so-- I was-- I was you know.

00:08:04.670 --> 00:08:06.390
I had been the Township supervisor.

00:08:06.390 --> 00:08:09.710
I started my career, political
career as a Township trustee

00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:11.010
for a short period of time.

00:08:11.010 --> 00:08:12.310
Then I became a supervisor
in Michigan.

00:08:12.310 --> 00:08:14.580
That's really like
being a Mayor right?

00:08:14.580 --> 00:08:17.370
And we had one of the larger
townships in the state.

00:08:17.370 --> 00:08:21.530
And so then I ran for
congress and-- lost.

00:08:21.530 --> 00:08:23.980
And-- that's the only
race that I've lost.

00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:26.980
But I recognize all the
reasons why I did loose.

00:08:26.980 --> 00:08:31.040
But anyway, then I-- was
still the Township Supervisor.

00:08:31.040 --> 00:08:32.580
I think I ran for one
more term after that.

00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:35.320
Then I was the County
Treasurer in Macomb County

00:08:35.320 --> 00:08:37.010
which you sometimes hear this term.

00:08:37.010 --> 00:08:38.870
The Reagan's-- Reagan democrats.

00:08:38.870 --> 00:08:40.740
That term had its genesis really

00:08:40.740 --> 00:08:43.300
