tomorrow night at the Fox Theatre

00:08:46.550 --> 00:08:48.310
with the Republican
Presidential debate.

00:08:48.310 --> 00:08:51.340
And-- when the dems
are in Flint on Sunday.

00:08:51.340 --> 00:08:53.280
They'll be talking a little
bit about Macomb County.

00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:55.530
Because it's about whether we
don't even know if we're democrats,

00:08:55.530 --> 00:08:57.190
republicans, what we
are half the time.

00:08:57.190 --> 00:08:58.620
We're like we're in a
Petri dish, you know?

00:08:58.620 --> 00:09:00.640
They're like, "What are they going
to-- what are they going to do?"

00:09:00.640 --> 00:09:03.010
But anyway, then I was the sec--

00:09:03.010 --> 00:09:04.970
Michigan secretary
of state for 8 years.

00:09:04.970 --> 00:09:08.520 position:56%
And we have term limits in Michigan.

00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:12.720 position:56%
And as secretary that's one of the 4
constitutional offices in the state.

00:09:12.720 --> 00:09:15.820
And so you know in term
limits it's a-- [Noise].

00:09:15.820 --> 00:09:17.400
&gt;&gt; Colleen Shogan: That's the
ghost of the members room.

00:09:17.400 --> 00:09:18.700
&gt;&gt; Rep. Candice Miller: Oh!

